Attachments: 2020.07.08,_subpoena_to Jacqueline_Hudkins_Attomey_at_Lawicorrected).docx 
Thanks so much,. I was actually able to scan my version of signature the other day. Attached is a subpoena 
from another case with that signature included. Would you please insert it into all of these subpoenas for the Korea case? 
Couple other corrections: 
• All of the riders appear to have a typo in the sentence beginning "A list of accounts hold, controlled, or accessible 
to the following individual(s) and/or entity(ies)," which should instead read "A list of accounts held controlled, or 
accessible to". Would you please fix that before sending out? 
• There are a couple instances in which the word "Alaska" is misspelled (it's written "Alaksa" in the riders). Would 
you please correct those? 
• Some of the riders have highlighting in them—would you please remove that? 
With those changes, these are good to go out. 
Thanks, 
From 
Sent: Thursday, July 9, 2020 4:29 PM 
To: 
Subject: Korea Bribery Subpoenas 
Hey 
I just took over paralegal duties from for this case. There were a number of riders that sent me and 
which I have turned into drafts of subpoenas. All of them are attached and in the drafts folder on the shared. 
• 
EFTA00020371
